      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HIJINKERY (1) hit the ground running off an inside draw last start and was never headed (22.49) at this track in a Grade 6 over 400m. Recorded the quickest time on the card last start. Can measure up again. COMPTON GYPSY (7) looks close to another win after finishing third last time (30.58) at Angle Park. Strike rate this distance strong having won 11 of 20 tries. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from four starts. Winning chance. SHE'S A JUMBO (5) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 1.5 lengths at Angle Park in a handy 30.72 beating Stomp And Run. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. Leading player again. ADHANA SNAPPY (2) was well fancied in betting last start but could only manage a nose away in second (30.69). Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Overdue and expected to feature again.",
